ğŸ“Œ PART 1: INSTALL UPTIME KUMA (Using Docker)
âœ… Step 1: Install Docker and Docker Compose (Ubuntu/Debian)
sudo apt update
sudo apt install docker.io docker-compose -y
sudo systemctl enable docker --now
âœ… Step 2: Create Uptime Kuma Project Folder
mkdir -p ~/uptime-kuma
cd ~/uptime-kuma
âœ… Step 3: Create docker-compose.yml File
nano docker-compose.yml
Paste the following:
version: '3'

services:
  uptime-kuma:
    image: louislam/uptime-kuma:latest
    container_name: uptime-kuma
    restart: always
    ports:
      - "3001:3001"
    volumes:
      - ./uptime-kuma-data:/app/data
Save and exit: Ctrl + O, Enter, Ctrl + X
âœ… Step 4: Start Uptime Kuma
docker-compose up -d
âœ… Step 5: Access Uptime Kuma Web UI
â€¢	Open browser and go to:
http://<your-server-ip>:3001
â€¢	Create an Admin Account (username & password)
