ğŸ“Œ PART 2: BASIC CONFIGURATION
âœ… Step 6: Create Monitor Group
1.	Click Group from the left sidebar.
2.	Click + Add New Group.
3.	Give a Name (e.g., "Websites", "Internal Services").
4.	Click Save.
âœ… Step 7: Add New Monitor
1.	Click the + Add New Monitor button.
2.	Fill the form:
o	Monitor Type: HTTP(s), Ping, Port, etc.
o	Friendly Name: e.g., My Website
o	URL / IP: e.g., https://example.com
o	Group: Select the previously created group.
o	Heartbeat Interval: e.g., 60 seconds
o	(Optional) Enable retry, upside down mode, etc.
3.	Click Save
________________________________________
ğŸ“Œ PART 3: TELEGRAM NOTIFICATION SETUP
âœ… Step 8: Create a Telegram Bot
1.	Open Telegram
2.	Search @BotFather
3.	Type /newbot
4.	Follow prompts:
o	Bot name (e.g., UptimeKumaBot)
o	Bot username (must end in bot, e.g., mykumabot)
5.	After success, BotFather will give you a token â€” save it.
________________________________________
âœ… Step 9: Get Telegram Chat ID
1.	Start a chat with your bot: Search your bot by username and click Start.
2.	Now go to:
https://api.telegram.org/bot/getUpdates
(replace <your-bot-token>)
3.	You will see JSON output like:
"chat": {
  "id": 123456789,
  "first_name": "YourName",
  ...
}
Save the id â€” thatâ€™s your Chat ID.
________________________________________
âœ… Step 10: Add Telegram Notification in Uptime Kuma
1.	Go to Settings > Notification.
2.	Click + Add New Notification.
3.	Choose Telegram.
4.	Fill:
o	Bot Token: from BotFather
o	Chat ID: from getUpdates
o	Name: e.g., "Telegram Alert"
5.	Click Test, then Save.
________________________________________
âœ… Step 11: Assign Notification to Monitor
1.	Click the monitor name (e.g., My Website).
2.	Click the âš™ï¸ gear icon.
3.	Scroll down to â€œNotificationâ€.
4.	Choose the created Telegram notification from the list.
5.	Click Save.
